<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[467,576,1409,1434]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Aquilegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[467,576,1409,1434]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Aquilegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName authority="Engelm. ex A. Gray, T." authorityName="Engelm. ex A. Gray, T." box="[625,1118,1409,1434]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Thalictrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fendleri">
<emphasis box="[625,845,1409,1434]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Thalictrum fendleri</emphasis>
Engelm. ex 
<collectingRegion box="[991,1014,1410,1434]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">A</collectingRegion>
. Gray, 
<emphasis box="[1097,1118,1410,1433]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">T.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1126,1137,1409,1434]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">*</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Pursh (Spencer 1981)" authorityName="Pursh (Spencer" authorityYear="1981" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Thalictrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis box="[1137,1255,1409,1434]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">pubescens</emphasis>
Pursh (
<bibRefCitation pageId="76" pageNumber="77" refId="ref103345" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1981) A revisionary study of the leaf-mining flies (Agromyzidae) of California. University of California Division of Agricultural Sciences Special Publication, 3273, 1 - 489." type="journal article">Spencer 1981</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[231,373,1445,1470]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" refId="ref100959" refString="Frick, K. E. (1959) Synopsis of the species of agromyzid leaf miners described from North America. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 108, 347 - 465. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.108 - 3407.347" type="journal article">Frick (1959)</bibRefCitation>
reported rearing this species from cultivated varieties of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1026,1135,1445,1470]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Aquilegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1026,1135,1445,1470]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Aquilegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1191,1315,1445,1470]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Thalictrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1191,1315,1445,1470]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Thalictrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as from 
<taxonomicName authority="Fisch." authorityName="Fisch." box="[212,412,1481,1506]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Aquilegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="formosa">
<emphasis box="[212,336,1482,1506]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<collectingRegion box="[212,232,1482,1505]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">A</collectingRegion>
. formosa
</emphasis>
Fisch.
</taxonomicName>
ex DC., but some of his records may refer to 
<taxonomicName authority="Spencer (Spencer &amp; Steyskal 1986)" authorityName="Spencer (Spencer &amp; Steyskal" authorityYear="1986" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Phytomyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquilegivora">
<emphasis box="[929,1202,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Phytomyza aquilegivora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation pageId="76" pageNumber="77" refId="ref103519" refString="Spencer, K. A. &amp; Steyskal, G. C. (1986) Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. USDA Agricultural Research Service Agriculture Handbook, 638, 1 - 478. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 119606" type="journal article">Spencer (Spencer &amp; Steyskal 1986)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="76.[151,1436,1301,1866]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,1553,1578]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Leaf mine.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[348,447,1553,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 189–199" captionStartId="121.[151,264,1660,1683]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,193,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@121.[151,1437,193,1639]" captionTargetPageId="121" captionText="FIGURES 189–199. leaf mines; 189: Phytomyza hatfieldae spec. nov. in Osmorhiza claytonii; 190: P. hydrophyllivora spec. nov. in Hydrophyllum canadense; 191: P. hydrophyllivora in Hydrophyllum virginianum (yellow puparium at tip of leaf serration, upper right); 192: P. linnaeae (Griffiths) in Linnaea borealis (transmitted light); 193: P. loewii Hendel in Clematis virginiana; 194: P. minuscula Goureau in Thalictrum pubescens; 195: P. omlandi Scheffer &amp; Lonsdale in Gelsemium sempervirens; 196: P. palmeri spec. nov. in Symphoricarpos orbiculatus (transmitted light; puparium at upper left); 197: P. palustris spec. nov. in Micranthes pensylvanica; 198: same, five brown puparia in blisters on lower leaf surface (whitish object along left side of midrib is a coniopterygid cocoon); 199: P. penstemonis Spencer in Penstemon digitalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1452959/files/figure.png" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Fig. 194</figureCitation>
) According to 
<bibRefCitation box="[625,803,1554,1578]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" refId="ref103345" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1981) A revisionary study of the leaf-mining flies (Agromyzidae) of California. University of California Division of Agricultural Sciences Special Publication, 3273, 1 - 489." type="journal article">Spencer (1981)</bibRefCitation>
, an “irregular, upper surface linear mine, with frass in conspicuous black strips.” The mines we observed were greenish-white and became quite wide toward the end, with irregular margins. Frass was in discrete grains for the most part, with some short strips toward the end, and as the mines widened the frass grains ceased to form two distinct rows and became irregularly scattered. The larva exits through a slit in the lower epidermis. There are often several mines per leaflet (Ellis 2017).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="76" pageNumber="77" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="76.[151,1436,1301,1866]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1733,1758]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Puparium.</emphasis>
Compact, oval, shining orange, formed outside the mine, “normally adhering lightly to the leaf until dislodged by wind or rain” (
<bibRefCitation box="[524,683,1770,1794]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" refId="ref103345" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1981) A revisionary study of the leaf-mining flies (Agromyzidae) of California. University of California Division of Agricultural Sciences Special Publication, 3273, 1 - 489." type="journal article">Spencer 1981</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="76" pageNumber="77" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="76.[151,1436,1301,1866]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1805,1830]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[360,420,1806,1830]" name="United States of America" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">USA</collectingCountry>
: CA, *VT, WA; Europe. 
<bibRefCitation box="[703,844,1805,1830]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" refId="ref100959" refString="Frick, K. E. (1959) Synopsis of the species of agromyzid leaf miners described from North America. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 108, 347 - 465. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.108 - 3407.347" type="journal article">Frick (1959)</bibRefCitation>
additionally recorded this species from CT, DC, ID, IL, and IN, but some of these records may refer to 
<taxonomicName authority="Spencer (Spencer &amp; Steyskal 1986)" authorityName="Spencer (Spencer &amp; Steyskal" authorityYear="1986" box="[719,1401,1841,1866]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Phytomyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquilegivora">
<emphasis box="[719,992,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Phytomyza aquilegivora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[999,1401,1841,1866]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" refId="ref103519" refString="Spencer, K. A. &amp; Steyskal, G. C. (1986) Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. USDA Agricultural Research Service Agriculture Handbook, 638, 1 - 478. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 119606" type="journal article">Spencer (Spencer &amp; Steyskal 1986)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
